layout: default
meta:
  title: "Automotive Manufacturing Applications | FlowFuse"
  description: "FlowFuse is a platform-agnostic, low-code platform for building, deploying, and managing industrial applications for automotive manufacturers."
  faq:
    - question: "Do I need to replace my existing SCADA or MES?"
      answer: >
        No. FlowFuse is designed to complement your existing manufacturing software, not replace it. You can extend your current systems with custom applications for production monitoring, downtime tracking, quality, workflows, and reporting.
    - question: "Which industrial protocols does FlowFuse support?"
      answer: >
        FlowFuse supports a wide range of industrial and IT protocols, including OPC UA, MQTT, Modbus, Siemens S7, EtherNet/IP, databases, and REST APIs. With over 6,000 integrations, it can connect PLCs, manufacturing software, enterprise systems, cloud services, and thousands of other technologies.
    - question: "Is FlowFuse suitable for enterprise manufacturing?"
      answer: >
        Yes. FlowFuse includes enterprise capabilities such as role-based access control (RBAC), single sign-on (SSO), audit logging, centralized management, and self-hosted deployment options for large manufacturing organizations.
    - question: "Can FlowFuse be deployed on-premises?"
      answer: >
        Yes. FlowFuse supports on-premises, self-hosted, private cloud, and air-gapped deployments, allowing manufacturers to meet their security, compliance, and operational requirements.
    - question: "Can I build applications without extensive software development?"
      answer: >
        Yes. FlowFuse combines low-code development with FlowFuse AI, enabling engineering and manufacturing teams to build industrial applications faster. AI-powered expert assistance and agentic development help accelerate application creation, while developers retain full control to customize logic and integrations as needed.
